'''Abdallah bin Alawi''' was the [[Sultan]] (?[[Shiraz]]i) of and on [[Anjouan]] island (in the Comoros) from 1816 to 1832, and then again from 1833 to his death in 1836. He was succeeded first by [[Ali bin Salim]], and finally by [[Saidi Alawi bin Abdallah]].

