'''Abu Tahir Khosrovani''' ({{lang-fa|ابو طاهر خسروانی}}) was a 10th-century [[Persian people|Persian]] who lived in the [[Samanid Empire]]. He was a native of [[Greater Khorasan|Khorasan]], and lived during the lifetime of the famous Persian poet [[Rudaki]]. Much of Abu Tahir's poetry, however, has disappeared and only a few are in existence, which are quoted by several Persian poets such as [[Asadi Tusi]]. Abu Tahir later died in 953.

